        <details>
            <summary id="1">What to do in a Cog Battle</summary>
            <h2>Cog Crossing</h2>
            <p>
                Try not to cross when chosing cogs to hit. Meaning, if you are positioned on the left of the battle, 
                hit the cogs on the left side. Of course sometimes this is not always possible. This is to prevent 
                confusion for other toons in the battle, espcially with game lag and little time left to chose a gag. 
                This tip is very important in Cog Golf courses as well. 
            </p>
            <h2>Sound vs. Lure</h2>
            <p>
                I am sure every toon has seen the SpeedChat phrase "Don't use sound on lured cogs!". This is a very important
                tip, because if violated, it could jeoprodize the whole battle. If, for exampe, sound is used on a round
                of four lured cogs, then all of those cogs get pushed back and will attack the toons. Sound also do not
                have jump back damage and will take away any jump back damage given by gags that come after sound. No good!
            </p>
        </details>
    </div>
</div>
